modules.description: This module provides functions to retrieve the current time as a POSIX clock value in days and picoseconds since the epoch, query the local time zone offset in seconds, and determine the clock's period in days and picoseconds. It works with integer and int64 values to represent time with picosecond precision. Concrete use cases include time-stamping events with high precision, adjusting for local time zones, and measuring clock resolution for timing-sensitive operations.

This module provides functions to retrieve monotonic time values in nanoseconds, specifically `elapsed_ns` to measure time since an arbitrary starting point and `period_ns` to get the clock's resolution if available. It works with 64-bit integers to represent time durations and optionally returns the clock's period. Concrete use cases include profiling code execution and measuring time intervals where clock drift must be avoided.
